          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Andreas Dilger",
          "email": "andreas.dilger@intel.com",
          "date": "2013-02-02 00:22:13.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Bobi Jam",
          "email": "bobijam.xu@intel.com",
          "date": "2013-02-04 01:41:50.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-1484 lprocfs: handle hidden proc_dir_entry users",
        "message": "LU-1484 lprocfs: handle hidden proc_dir_entry users\n\nThe RHEL 5.9 2.6.18-348.1.1.el5 kernel uses both the new style\n\"pde_users\" and the old style \"deleted\" flags for marking a\nproc_dir_entry as deleted.  Unfortunately, the new \"pde_users\"\ndata is hidden in an external structure that is not visible to\nthe callers or in the headers (for binary compatibility I guess?)\nso our configure checks cannot find it.\n\nInstead, just check for proc_fops == NULL in a racy manner on\nsuch kernels, since we cannot do locking and the locking is\nmostly just needed as a memory barrier since pde_fops could\nbecome NULL at any time after dropping the lock.\n\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I05cae305e24ffff09a06e3ad17c28c175c3ebbe5\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b1_8"
    }
  },
